rComments: The guy is pretty young and super passionate about math. He's not the best at teaching, he mumbles here and there, however, if you ask him to repeat/clarify something, he gladly will. The course itself is pretty challenging; make sure to read the chapter and do the homework beforehand to get a better understanding from the lecture. Great guy :)
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class', 'Caring']

rComments: This guy is absolutely hilarious and endearing to watch. He gets very excited about math which is always nice to see. He explains everything very clearly, and will reopen TopHat for everyone. Highly recommend taking a class with him.

He defs doesn't look it but he's an amazing prof. Hilarious and absolutely adorable personality. Shy bean probs but avoids eye contact like 94% of the time with any kind of human being. Makes to lectures on time even during the midst of snowstorm (RESPECT) even understands if students don't show up. Would defs take again if I have to take math.

Don't be fooled by his youthful appearance, he's really good at teaching and is quite humorous. He doesn't spoon-feed you. he'd give you a question, let you have a go at it, give you a clue, let you go at it again then go through the entire question and will explain everything clearly.
